               <msContents>
                  <summary>A Demotic marriage contract between husband and wife, whose names are
                     lost along with the signatures and the witnesses.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="egy-Egyd" source="#TM">Egyptian in Demotic script</textLang>

               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>Three large adjoining fragments, and a very small piece loose at the bottom of
                     the papyrus as framed. Gaps are present where the segments of papyrus adjoin,
                     as well as within the fragments themselves. In addition, several words are
                     entirely missing, or only partly preserved due to the rubbing off of the
                     ink.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="scroll">
                     <supportDesc material="papyrus">
                        <support>papyrus</support>
                        <extent>Four fragments of papyrus of which three are joint and a smaller one
                           is separate. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>163</height>
                              <width>137</width>
                           </dimensions><dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>13</height>
                              <width>18</width>
                           </dimensions></extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>Likely written by one scribe, all in black ink.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>No vignette accompanies the text on these fragments.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>


               </physDesc>
